               <head>Sufi tales, untitled</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Untitled collection of eighty-six brief Sufi edifying tales or ḥikāyāt by an unnamed author.</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1220x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled collection of eighty-six brief Sufi edifying tales or ḥikāyāt by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work lacks a preface or thematic arrangement. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 23v): completed by Sayyid Ṣamīm ʿAlī known as Sayyid Murād ʿAlī ibn ʿĀshiq ʿAlī at Masjid-i Panjābiyān, 6 Z̲ī al-Qaʿdah 1237/25 July 1822. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Not foliated. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding. 
</p>
                        <p>Paper dust wrapper (draft BEIC legal publication for Fort William, Home Department, Legislative, dated 4 April 1850); watermark (J Whatman, 1848); torn, creased, and stained. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound, cropped; stains, wormholes. 
</p>
                        <p>Loose letter between folios 10-11. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
